Test::Portability::Files
========================

DESCRIPTION

    This module is used to check the portability across operating systems 
    of the names of the files present in the distribution of a module. 
    The checks use the advices given in perlport. 
    The author of the distribution can select which points to test. 


INSTALLATION

    To install this module, run the following commands:

        perl Makefile.PL
        make
        make test
        make install

    Alternatively, to install with Module::Build, you can use the 
    following commands:

        perl Build.PL
        ./Build
        ./Build test
        ./Build install


